SEARCH ALGORITHMS# Linear Search# Linear search goes over all elements and checks if it is the target element.
Since the search has to go through all elements in the worst case where there the values is not there, it has a complexity of $O(n)$.
// golang package search func Linear(items []int, target int) bool { for _, n := range items { if n == target { return true } } return false } Binary Search# Binary search is used to find items in an ordered list by iteratively halving the input.
